               <head>Makhzan-i Afghānī by Khvājah Niʻmat Allāh</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh85001521 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh90002018">
                  <summary>A shorter recension of his <title>Tārīk̲h̲ i K̲h̲ān-Jahānī va
								Mak̲h̲zan i Afg̲h̲ānī,</title> a history of the Afg̲h̲āns by Khvājah
							Niʻmat Allāh, fl. 1613-1630
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_592-item1">
                     <author key="viaf_35539655">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Khvājah Niʻmat Allāh ibn Khvājah
									Ḥabīb Allāh Haravī (fl. 1613-1630)</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">خواجه نعمت الله بن خواجه حبيب الله
									هروی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2545"> Makhzan-i
								Afghānī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">مخزن افغانی</title>
                     <colophon>Copied for Shaykh Muḥammad Isḥāq by Sujān Singh, writer
								(navīsandah), resident of Nakodar, Punjab (f. 59v) between 15th
								Shaʻban regnal year 29 of Aurangzeb (7 July 1686) and (f. 206r) the
								last day of Ramazan regnal year 30 (20 August 1686) in the qaṣbah
								Vādī(?) in the parganah of Nagmīr(?).</colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Copy defective at both ends. </p>
                        <p>Contents: bāb 3 (f. 12r); daftar 1 (f. 27r); daftar 2 (f. 60r);
									daftar 3 (f. 154r); khāṭimah (f. 206v). </p>
                        <p>Colophons on ff. 59v, 153v and 206r. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
